Method Detail

parseDate

public static java.util.Date parseDate(java.lang.String dateString)
                                throws java.text.ParseException
Parses the specified date string into a java.util.Date object using English locale (which is what Dimensions uses on most databases in most versions), and the local timezone.

This method tries to parse a date using three date patterns, in the following order of preference:

  1. dd-MMM-yyyy HH:mm:ss
  2. dd-MM-yyyy HH:mm:ss
  3. yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss
  4. yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss.SSS
If the date string cannot be parsed using any of these patterns, a ParseException will be thrown.

Parameters:
dateString - the date string to be parsed
Returns:
the corresponding java.util.Date object
Throws:
java.text.ParseException - if the specifed date string could not be parsed as a java.util.Date using any of the three Dimensions date patterns

                                       java.util.Locale locale)
                                throws java.text.ParseException
Parses the specified date string into a java.util.Date object using specified locale (which, if needed, will be the locale of the Oracle database instance), and the local timezone.

This method tries to parse a date using three date patterns, in the following order of preference:

  1. dd-MMM-yyyy HH:mm:ss
  2. dd-MM-yyyy HH:mm:ss
  3. yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss
  4. yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss.SSS
If the date string cannot be parsed using any of these patterns, a ParseException will be thrown.

Parameters:
dateString - the date string to be parsed
locale - the locale to interpret the short month names with
Returns:
the corresponding java.util.Date object
Throws:
java.text.ParseException - if the specifed date string could not be parsed as a java.util.Date using any of the three Dimensions date patterns

Generates contents of the deployment view entry page (self-submitting form) and saves it in existing given file.

Parameters:
conn - - Dimensions connection.
view - - subtab of the deployment view. Possible values are 'Pending', 'Archived', 'History', 'Rollback' and 'Queue'.
rootOrProject - - root or project specification.
stage - - stage in the path to the node in the deployment view tree.
area - - area in the path to the node in the deployment view tree.
projectOfArea - - project in the path to the node in the deployment view tree.
objectSpec -
objectId - - this field will select the node in the deployment view tree.
format -
userFile - - existing file name to save the generated contents to.
Returns:
true if success, false otherwise.
